    <h3>About Sofia</h3>
    <p>Last year, Sofia was voted the host for EuRuKo 2016. Sofia is the capital of Bulgaria, and also the largest city in the country.
      It's located right in the centre of the Balkan Peninsula, at the foot of Vitosha mountain.
      With more than 7000 years of history it's one of the oldest cities in Europe. </p>

    <p>One can easily find their way around Sofia by means of the underground subway. It has two lines and 34 stations,
      making possible traveling between the city center and the airport in around 30 minutes for less than 1 euro.
      Apart from visiting all the historical and cultural sights, you can also enjoy a walk in Sofiaâ€™s
